  <Placemark>
   <name>Gale Warning issued October 4 at 1:05PM PDT until October 5 at 11:00AM PDT by NWS Eureka CA</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_moderate</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, north winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and seas 7 to 9 feet expected. For the Small
Craft Advisory, north winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt
and seas 5 to 7 feet.

* WHERE...Pt St George to Cape Mendocino 10 to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 3 AM to 11 AM PDT Sunday.
For the Small Craft Advisory, until 3 AM PDT Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.</Snippet>
   <ExtendedData>
