  <Placemark>
   <name>Small Craft Advisory issued October 4 at 3:53PM EDT until October 5 at 2:00PM EDT by NWS Marquette MI</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 10 to 20 kt
with gusts up to 30 kt and waves 1 to 4 ft. For the Gale
Watch, southwest winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and
waves 4 to 7 ft possible.

* WHERE...Ontonagon to Upper Entrance of Portage Canal MI and
Upper Entrance of Portage Canal to Eagle River MI.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 2 PM EDT Sunday.
For the Gale Watch, from Sunday afternoon through late Sunday
night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.</Snippet>
